  "signature": "ed25519:9b1d4f7a2e6c3085b4f1d9a7e2c5083b6f4d1a9e7c2b5083f6d4a1e9c7b2053a",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must have documented verification tests and version-controlled source; all numerical routines traceable to published benchmarks.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 used with documented QA procedures including regression test suite and ISO 9001-certified development process. Achieved level meets required level for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least two canonical benchmark problems relevant to rotating machinery flows.",
      "rationale": "Code verified against lid-driven cavity and rotating disk benchmark cases. Order-of-accuracy testing confirms second-order spatial convergence for the momentum equations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis index QoI; discretization error must be quantified and shown to be below 10% of nominal predicted value.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (3.2M, 9.1M, 24.6M cells). GCI for hemolysis index is 4.7%, well within acceptance threshold. Richardson extrapolation applied to confirm asymptotic convergence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match or bound the computational boundary conditions within documented uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental data collected at 2500 RPM and flow rates 2.5–7.0 L/min. CFD boundary conditions set to match experimental inlet/outlet conditions within 2% flow rate uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA pump experimental values. Mean absolute error of 8.3% across operating points, within combined uncertainty of 12%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must be directly linked to the clinical harm mechanism of erythrocyte damage.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis and volume-averaged scalar shear stress selected as primary QoIs, directly corresponding to erythrocyte damage mechanisms relevant to CPB-associated hemolytic complications."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry and fluid (bovine blood or validated blood analog) as the intended COU operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed using FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with bovine blood at 37°C, matching the intended CPB operating scenario. Rotational speed and flow rate ranges overlap with worst-case COU envelope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; default acceptance at gradation 1 is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, numerical solver error beyond code verification is not required. The factor is acknowledged but formal round-off and iterative convergence error decomposition is outside the scope of this assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification documentation sufficient at this risk level.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Analysts hold relevant CFD and biofluid mechanics credentials. Formal use-error analysis is deferred to higher MRL assessments."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model must be justified by published literature for blood pump applications.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating blood pump geometries. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied with literature-derived coefficients validated for erythrocyte damage prediction."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood viscosity, density, and hematocrit must be documented with uncertainty ranges; sensitivity of QoI to input variation must be characterized.",
      "rationale": "Blood modeled as non-Newtonian fluid using Carreau model with hematocrit 40±2%. Sensitivity analysis shows hemolysis index varies less than 5% across the documented input uncertainty range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for computational-primary assessment; experimental sample characterization addressed under test conditions factor.",
      "rationale": "Formal test sample characterization beyond what is captured in the test conditions factor is not required at MRL 2. Blood sample provenance documented in the experimental dataset metadata."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; equivalency addressed qualitatively through test conditions and model inputs factors.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency mapping between validation experiment parameters and COU parameters is not required at MRL 2. Qualitative equivalency is addressed within the test conditions and model inputs assessments above."
    }
  ],
